steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"drrhg","text":"Drain medium and gently wash cells once with ice-cold PBS (0.5ml for mw6; 1 ml for 6-cm dish; 3 ml for 10-cm dish).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fbcrc","text":"Use a gentle stream to dislodge cells with PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d8086","text":"Centrifuge the tube at 3000 x g for 1 min and discard the supernatant.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4oviq","text":"Resuspend pellet of cells with 500 μl of ice-cold IP buffer","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"17k0j","text":"Lyse the cells by sonication: 3 times 10’’/30% on ice, waiting 1 minute in between for the lysate to cool down","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"47iui","text":"Incubate the whole cell lysate on an end-to-end rocker at 4°C/30’ to solubilize the membrane proteins.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bgsns","text":"Spin down at 14,000 x g for 10 minutes at 4°C to pellet debris and genomic DNA, save the supernatant.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"drtlh","text":"Save 75 µl, Cell Lysate (CL) and add 25 µl of SB4X","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9me79","text":"Mix total proteins (equal amounts for each sample) with 10-20 µl of Protein G beads and 2 µg of specific antibody. Note: wash Protein G Beads 3 times with PBS to remove ethanol present in the storage buffer. Let equilibrate in IP buffer for minute before use.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ceb6","text":"Separate the beads and save 75 µl of Flow Through (FT) and add 2 µl of SB4X","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fv5v8","text":"10.   Wash beads 3 times with 1 ml of IP buffer","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c6ok4","text":"12.   Warm samples at 42°C/10’ (membrane proteins would start to aggregate at higher temperature).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3rid9","text":"13.   Load 10 µl of each sample per well for SDS-PAGE","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
